The paper deals with the area requirements of planar straight-line orthogonal drawings of ternary trees, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the study of the structure of ternary trees, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The experimental evaluation and conjecture on the area requirements involve combinatorial methods and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses upper bounds and lower bounds, which are topics in graph theory (cs.GR) and computational complexity (cs.DC), respectively.
